ChildCategories.Name: Heat Shrink Tubing
ChildCategories.SeoDescription: Heat Shrink Tubing are hollow tubes of woven material with both ends open. These tubes become smaller in size as they warmed by hot air or a flame. Most often used as insulation material when connecting wires together, these tubes can be used to group wires together, or insulate items from mechanical wear plus a lot more. Category.SeoDescription: Products within the cable and wire management category are used for physically organizing, protecting, installing, or identifying electrical or fiber optic conductors and cables. ChildCategories.Name: Heat Shrink Tubing
ChildCategories.SeoDescription: Heat Shrink Tubing are hollow tubes of woven material with both ends open. These tubes become smaller in size as they warmed by hot air or a flame. Most often used as insulation material when connecting wires together, these tubes can be used to group wires together, or insulate items from mechanical wear plus a lot more. The shrinking ratio ranges from 1.2:1 to 6:1 with lengths from 0.031’ (9.52mm, 0.38”) to 6562.0’ (2000.0m) and an inner diameter ranges of 0.014” (0.36mm) to 11.220” (284.99mm).

These include but are not limited to bushings, grommets, and cable grips to protect cordage passing through an enclosure wall from damage, cable ties and split loom or spiral wrap sleeving for physically bundling installed cables together, printable and pre-printed lables and clip-on markers for identification, and cable trays & raceways for serviceable routing of cable systems within a physical facility such as a data center or office building.

ChildCategories.Name: Heat Shrink Tubing
ChildCategories.SeoDescription: Heat Shrink Tubing are hollow tubes of woven material with both ends open. These tubes become smaller in size as they warmed by hot air or a flame. Most often used as insulation material when connecting wires together, these tubes can be used to group wires together, or insulate items from mechanical wear plus a lot more. The shrinking ratio ranges from 1.2:1 to 6:1 with lengths from 0.031’ (9.52mm, 0.38”) to 6562.0’ (2000.0m) and an inner diameter ranges of 0.014” (0.36mm) to 11.220” (284.99mm).

Description.DetailedDescription: Heat Shrink Tubing, Flexible 0.750" (19.05mm) 3 to 1 Red 4.00' (1.22m)

Parameters.ValueText: Adhesive Lined, Corrosion Resistant, Flame Retardant, Fluid Resistant, Self Extinguishing, Water Resistant

Examples include wire of a common gauge in various colors, timing crystals of different frequencies, resistors or inductors of assorted values, fuses of different sizes and current ratings, heat shrinkable tubing of different sizes, LEDs in varying colors, and others.

ChildCategories.Name: Heat Shrink Tubing Kits
ChildCategories.SeoDescription: Products in this family are assortments of heat shrinkable insulating tubing, from a single manufacturer and product series but varying in size and/or color, offered in kit form to provide a convenient means of acquiring a range of product likely to be found useful in the course of maintenance, repair, or product development operations. Different product series exhibit different characteristics, such as maximum ratio of pre- and post-shrink diameters, mechanical rigidity of the product after shrinking, and presence of an inner adhesive layer.
